WEBVTT

00:05.172 --> 00:07.241
[newsman]
Good evening, New Yorkers,

00:07.274 --> 00:09.710
and welcome to
Channel 8 News, Live at 7.

00:09.743 --> 00:12.313
-I'm Ted Spinelli.
-And I'm Lisa Lipton.

00:12.346 --> 00:14.515
A big day in news
across the city,

00:14.548 --> 00:16.450
but we begin in Staten Island,

00:16.483 --> 00:19.086
where a water main break in the
West New Brighton neighborhood

00:19.119 --> 00:21.589
left the streets looking
more like rivers.

00:21.622 --> 00:24.224
Joanna Roscoe is live
from Staten Island now.

00:24.257 --> 00:25.593
That's right, Lisa.

00:25.626 --> 00:28.095
This was the scene
just hours ago

00:28.128 --> 00:31.732
on what is usually considered
a quiet residential street.

00:31.765 --> 00:33.601
Now, as you can see behind me,

00:33.634 --> 00:35.569
city workers have
managed to stop

00:35.602 --> 00:37.271
the street-level flooding,

00:37.304 --> 00:40.174
but underground flooding
still remains a concern.

00:40.207 --> 00:41.742
Oh, boy. That means
a messy commute home

00:41.775 --> 00:43.777
for a few Staten Islanders,
right, Joanna?

00:43.810 --> 00:45.212
Yeah, it sure does.

00:45.245 --> 00:46.747
Now I am here with
a local resident

00:46.780 --> 00:49.283
who has been watching
the situation closely.

00:49.316 --> 00:50.718
His name is Nandor...

00:50.751 --> 00:52.686
Nandor the Relentless.

00:52.719 --> 00:54.488
Nandor De Laurentis.

00:54.521 --> 00:57.191
Now, Nandor, you live in
this neighborhood, correct?

00:57.224 --> 00:59.159
Yes, that's right, Joanna, I do.

00:59.192 --> 01:00.761
In that house just over there.

01:00.794 --> 01:03.397
With my friends. It's fun.

01:03.430 --> 01:05.132
Great.

01:05.165 --> 01:07.301
And as I understand,
you were on the street

01:07.334 --> 01:09.069
when the water main broke.
Can you tell us about that?

01:09.102 --> 01:10.337
[Nandor]
Yes, I can, Joanna.

01:10.370 --> 01:12.373
I was going
for my evening stroll,

01:12.406 --> 01:14.141
which I do for my mental health

01:14.174 --> 01:16.043
as well as for
my physical health,

01:16.076 --> 01:18.078
and then,
all of a sudden, crash!

01:18.111 --> 01:20.414
Burst!

01:20.447 --> 01:21.782
Water, it shoots

01:21.815 --> 01:23.584
into the air, and then, like,

01:23.617 --> 01:25.386
all over the street.

01:25.419 --> 01:26.687
[Joanna] Now, Nandor,
have you seen an incident

01:26.720 --> 01:29.123
in this area like this before?

01:29.156 --> 01:32.393
Not since the great
flood in 1892, Joanna.

01:32.426 --> 01:34.194
That was a big boy.

01:34.227 --> 01:35.796
[chuckles] 1892.

01:35.829 --> 01:39.700
Oh, silly me. Not... not 1892.

01:39.733 --> 01:43.037
-[laughs]
-1992.

01:43.070 --> 01:45.773
Yeah, I was gonna say, uh, 1892?

01:45.806 --> 01:48.509
Give me this guy's
skin care secrets.

01:48.542 --> 01:51.478
Because 1892 was
a year that was not

01:51.511 --> 01:53.447
in my, uh, human lifespan,

01:53.480 --> 01:56.584
but 1992 most definitely was.

01:56.617 --> 01:58.552
It's 2023 now...

01:58.585 --> 02:01.121
-Right.
-...and it was 1992 then.

02:01.154 --> 02:02.656
And I have been living
in Staten Island

02:02.689 --> 02:04.258
for many centuries.

02:04.291 --> 02:05.593
Many centuries.

02:05.626 --> 02:08.629
Well, it looks like
we have discovered

02:08.662 --> 02:11.465
the secret to eternal life.

02:11.498 --> 02:14.134
-Now, I do have a...
-[whimpers, mutters]

02:14.167 --> 02:17.238
Well, Ted and Lisa,
I will be here,

02:17.271 --> 02:19.540
on the ground,
monitoring the situation

02:19.573 --> 02:21.575
as it develops. Back to you.

02:21.608 --> 02:24.745
Oh, shitty shit. I fucked it.

02:24.778 --> 02:27.081
["You're Dead"
by Norma Tanega playing]

02:27.114 --> 02:29.483
♪ Don't sing if you want
to live long ♪

02:29.516 --> 02:32.086
♪ They have no use
for your song ♪

02:32.119 --> 02:34.622
♪ You're dead, you're dead,
you're dead ♪

02:34.655 --> 02:37.557
♪ You're dead
and out of this world ♪

02:39.192 --> 02:42.229
♪ Now your hope and compassion
is gone ♪

02:42.262 --> 02:44.832
♪ You sold out your dream
to the world ♪

02:44.865 --> 02:47.268
♪ Stay dead, stay dead,
stay dead ♪

02:47.301 --> 02:49.370
♪ You're dead
and out of this world. ♪

02:49.403 --> 02:51.605
