02:59.446 --> 03:01.782
[Nandor] Shit, shit,
shit, shit, shit, shit, shit.

03:01.815 --> 03:03.417
-[Laszlo] From the diaphragm.
-[Doll Nadja vocalizing]

03:03.450 --> 03:04.418
[Nandor]
Shit, shit, shit, shit, shit.

03:04.451 --> 03:06.253
Guillermo!

03:06.286 --> 03:07.821
Gizmo is not here.

03:07.854 --> 03:10.157
Colin Robinson,
turn on the television.

03:10.190 --> 03:11.258
Channel 8.

03:11.291 --> 03:12.593
Your arms broken?

03:12.626 --> 03:14.361
-Please!
-[groans]

03:14.394 --> 03:15.462
All right.

03:15.495 --> 03:16.830
[man]
This is go...

03:16.863 --> 03:18.332
[Joanna]
But there is some worry that...

03:18.365 --> 03:19.733
-Huh.
-[Nandor groans]

03:19.766 --> 03:21.569
That's our street. Huh.
Well, that's neat.

03:21.602 --> 03:23.037
That is not neat.

03:23.070 --> 03:24.438
I may have committed

03:24.471 --> 03:27.441
an unforgivable
and irreversible blunder.

03:27.474 --> 03:29.743
Okay, Nandor, don't get
your knickers in a twist.

03:29.776 --> 03:32.146
I-I accidentally told
this Joanna Roscoe

03:32.179 --> 03:35.282
that we have lived in this
street for many centuries.

03:35.315 --> 03:36.550
-[gasps]
-You did what?

03:36.583 --> 03:39.086
And now she and
all of the viewers

03:39.119 --> 03:41.322
of Channel 8 News Live at 7

03:41.355 --> 03:43.490
know that we are vampires.

03:43.523 --> 03:45.125
-[shouting]
-And now--

03:45.158 --> 03:46.694
And now all of the humans
are going to

03:46.727 --> 03:48.295
drive us out of Staten Island

03:48.328 --> 03:49.463
like they drove us
out of the Old Country.

03:49.496 --> 03:51.765
[Laszlo]
Alea iacta est.

03:51.798 --> 03:53.567
-Game over.
-[plays piano sting]

03:53.600 --> 03:55.736
No, no!

03:55.769 --> 03:57.271
This time, we fight!

03:57.304 --> 03:59.472
This is our last stand!

04:00.807 --> 04:02.676
-Who's with me?
-Me!

04:04.244 --> 04:05.813
Silence!

04:05.846 --> 04:07.615
I have a plan.

04:07.648 --> 04:10.584
I think we should
kill Joanna Roscoe.

04:10.617 --> 04:13.320
And what would that solve?

04:13.353 --> 04:15.255
Do you have any better ideas?

04:16.290 --> 04:18.158
Where is Guillermo?!

04:18.191 --> 04:19.526
[dings]

04:19.559 --> 04:22.229
So, yeah, tonight's kind of
a farewell,

04:22.262 --> 04:23.731
goodbye dinner
for me and my mom.

04:23.764 --> 04:25.332
She doesn't know
that it's a goodbye,

04:25.365 --> 04:27.101
but when I become
a full vampire,

04:27.134 --> 04:28.402
it won't be safe for my family,

04:28.435 --> 04:30.571
or for me because

04:30.604 --> 04:32.806
they are vampire killers,

04:32.839 --> 04:34.742
and I'll be a vampire.

04:34.775 --> 04:36.243
[sighs] It's kind of heavy,
actually,

04:36.276 --> 04:38.579
if you think about it.

04:38.612 --> 04:40.247
No one imagines
they'll have to say

04:40.280 --> 04:42.182
a final goodbye
to their mom, but...

04:42.215 --> 04:44.151
here we are.

04:44.184 --> 04:45.686
-Mami.
-[speaking Spanish]

04:45.719 --> 04:48.355
Oh. Oh, everyone's here.
I thought it was just going

04:48.388 --> 04:49.723
-to be you and me.
-Hi.

04:49.756 --> 04:52.126
Oh, Tía. Wow, you're also here.

04:52.159 --> 04:54.795
[speaking Spanish]

04:54.828 --> 04:56.697
You hungry? You hungry?

04:56.730 --> 04:59.133
Hey, Memo.

04:59.166 --> 05:00.534
These guys are still
doing that documentary

05:00.567 --> 05:02.236
on losers who work
at the railroad, huh?

05:02.269 --> 05:03.571
-All right.
-Ah, I'm just playing.

05:03.604 --> 05:04.705
-Okay.
-Hey, we're putting my tía's

05:04.738 --> 05:06.574
-gifts right there.
-Hmm?

05:06.607 --> 05:08.576
The gifts.

05:08.609 --> 05:12.246
Wait, you didn't bring a gift
for your own mama's birthday?

05:12.279 --> 05:13.514
[Guillermo]
So, funny thing.

05:13.547 --> 05:15.149
In the middle of, uh,

05:15.182 --> 05:17.051
making it a big day about me,

05:17.084 --> 05:20.387
I totally forgot that
it's a big day for her.

05:20.420 --> 05:22.556
It's her birthday,

05:22.589 --> 05:25.192
but birthday or no,
I need to do this.

05:25.225 --> 05:27.294
Mami, Mami.

05:27.327 --> 05:28.562
[speaks Spanish]

05:28.595 --> 05:29.663
Can I talk to you
in private, please?

05:29.696 --> 05:32.532
[speaks Spanish]

05:34.401 --> 05:37.571
[Joanna]
...local resident Nandor,
who has some insights.

05:37.604 --> 05:41.275
[Guillermo speaking Spanish]

05:41.308 --> 05:43.344
[exclaims in Spanish]

05:43.377 --> 05:45.346
[Joanna]
...part of a pattern of
local infrastructure failures?

05:45.379 --> 05:47.614
Yes, Joanna. If I may...

05:51.818 --> 05:54.054
To the millions
and millions of viewers

05:54.087 --> 05:57.091
of Channel 8 News Live at 7,

05:57.124 --> 05:59.059
you will forget...

05:59.092 --> 06:01.395
[Ted]
Apologies to Joanna
and Mr. De Laurentis,

06:01.428 --> 06:04.064
but we have some breaking news.

06:04.097 --> 06:05.499
The National Weather Service
has announced

06:05.532 --> 06:07.701
a severe thunderstorm
warning for the city.

06:07.734 --> 06:10.070
We now go to meteorologist
Heather Dupont...

06:10.103 --> 06:13.641
[shouting in Spanish]

06:13.674 --> 06:15.442
[speaking Spanish]

06:16.243 --> 06:18.712
[whispers] I leave the house
for one fucking minute...

06:18.745 --> 06:20.347
[Miguel]
Memo!

06:20.380 --> 06:22.349
[speaking Spanish]

06:22.382 --> 06:25.085
[Guillermo sings in Spanish]

06:25.118 --> 06:27.221
[group laughing]

06:27.254 --> 06:29.155
[speaking Spanish]

06:30.557 --> 06:33.093
It's not a big deal,
as long as they just...

06:33.126 --> 06:34.361
answer the fucking phone.

06:34.394 --> 06:35.629
-[phone ringing]
-[Laszlo] Fucking hell.

06:35.662 --> 06:37.197
-[shouting]
-Damn!

06:37.230 --> 06:39.233
-Look out, look out!
-[Nadja whimpering]

06:39.266 --> 06:41.435
-[Laszlo] Oh, fuck this. Ah!
-[ringing]

06:41.468 --> 06:43.237
-Should I answer that?
-[Laszlo] Announcement.

06:43.270 --> 06:46.206
After methodical analysis,
I have decided

06:46.239 --> 06:47.575
that it is not a good idea

06:47.608 --> 06:49.643
to kill Joanna Roscoe.

06:49.676 --> 06:51.245
No shit, you human fart.

06:51.278 --> 06:53.113
Now, help me
booby-trap the staircase.

06:53.146 --> 06:54.582
Maybe I should just
take it off the hook?

06:54.615 --> 06:55.482
[Guillermo]
Hello?

06:55.515 --> 06:57.217
[line beeping]

06:57.250 --> 06:59.320
Colin Robinson, now is
not the time for decorating.

06:59.353 --> 07:00.654
Get your fucking go-bag.

07:00.687 --> 07:02.356
Vampires must always

07:02.389 --> 07:04.091
be prepared to skip out of town

07:04.124 --> 07:05.593
at a moment's notice.

07:05.626 --> 07:07.761
I have been chased out
of five, maybe six

07:07.794 --> 07:09.530
villages over the course
of my vampiric life,

07:09.563 --> 07:11.599
and believe me,
you don't want to be

07:11.632 --> 07:14.235
caught out there fleeing with
only the clothes on your back,

07:14.268 --> 07:16.437
sleeping at the bottom
of a cold well,

07:16.470 --> 07:18.072
sucking on the throats
of the mountain goats

07:18.105 --> 07:19.340
you once called your brothers.

07:19.373 --> 07:21.709
No. So, what was
the first thing I did

07:21.742 --> 07:23.077
when I moved to Staten Island?

07:23.110 --> 07:24.511
I made the go-bags.

07:24.544 --> 07:27.214
[Laszlo]
I have decided on
a multi-part plan.

07:27.247 --> 07:28.315
The first part of which:

07:28.348 --> 07:30.718
Kidnap Joanna Roscoe.

07:30.751 --> 07:32.086
And how is that going to help?

07:32.119 --> 07:33.487
Takes us to step two.

07:33.520 --> 07:35.356
-[bees buzzing]
-[Nadja groans] Everybody,

07:35.389 --> 07:37.224
in your go-bags you will find

07:37.257 --> 07:39.226
your emergency
fleeing checklist.

07:39.259 --> 07:40.227
Okay.

07:40.260 --> 07:41.762
"Ancestral soils."

07:41.795 --> 07:42.796
Check.

07:42.829 --> 07:45.232
"Three days' supply of blood."

07:45.265 --> 07:46.500
Eh... Oof.

07:46.533 --> 07:48.602
A little bit rank, but check.

07:48.635 --> 07:51.305
"Memorize new identity."
[clears throat]

07:51.338 --> 07:52.606
[American accent]
"Oh, hello.

07:52.639 --> 07:54.308
"My name is Sally Rhubarb.

07:54.341 --> 07:57.211
"I am a blonde girl
from a large farm,

07:57.244 --> 08:01.615
and my blackberry pie wins
every year at the county fair."

08:01.648 --> 08:02.616
-Don't sit there.
-Why not?

08:02.649 --> 08:04.017
Because.

08:05.385 --> 08:07.755
-[gasps]
-The whole ground floor
is booby-trapped

08:07.788 --> 08:09.490
for our final stand.

08:09.523 --> 08:11.058
Oh, yes, because the attackers
first thing they will do

08:11.091 --> 08:12.526
